<paragraph id="8B9036A069588F5FFF4BFB2EFC4F8143" blockId="18.[151,1437,1086,2013]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB269588F5FFF4BFB2EFEFF80FE" bold="true" box="[199,349,1230,1256]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Recognition.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2369588F5FFE6FFB2FFDED80FF" authority="Burington, 2022" authorityName="Burington" authorityYear="2022" box="[483,591,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Eucelatoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inclani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB269588F5FFE6FFB2FFDED80FF" box="[483,591,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">E. inclani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95BEAB269588F5FFDD8FB2FFD0E80FF" bold="true" box="[596,684,1231,1257]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26857C969588F5FFDD8FB2FFD0E80FF" box="[596,684,1231,1257]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
share with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2369588F5FFCA6FB2FFC2380FF" authorityName=": Wood" authorityYear="1985" box="[810,897,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Eucelatoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferox">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB269588F5FFCA6FB2FFC2380FF" box="[810,897,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">E. ferox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the unique condition of two parallel longitudinal vittae on the thoracic notum paired with the long, nearly abdomen-length piercer. The 
<typeStatus id="5494880269588F5FFBC2FB13FB12811B" box="[1102,1200,1267,1293]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2369588F5FFB5EFB13FA9C811B" authority="Burington, 2022" authorityName="Burington" authorityYear="2022" box="[1234,1342,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Eucelatoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inclani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB269588F5FFB5EFB13FA9C811B" box="[1234,1342,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">E. inclani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B95BEAB269588F5FFAC8FB13FA3E811B" bold="true" box="[1348,1436,1267,1293]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A26857C969588F5FFAC8FB13FA3E811B" box="[1348,1436,1267,1293]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs in that the ocellar setae are minute, indistinguishable from the surrounding setulae of the ocellar triangle, the entirety of the head tomentum is yellow, and the calypters are orange-tinted.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C335652B69588F5FFF4BFABFFA2B818B" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9036A069588F5FFF4BFABFFA2B818B" blockId="18.[151,1437,1086,2013]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB269588F5FFF4BFABFFEEC816F" bold="true" box="[199,334,1375,1401]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named for the collector, Dr. Diego J. Inclán, Ecuadorian tachinidologist and ecologist, who was also responsible for recent work on the 
<taxonomicName id="4C2F4D2369588F5FFDDEFA63FC188188" authority="(Wulp)" baseAuthorityName="Wulp" box="[594,954,1411,1438]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Eucelatoria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obrumbrata">
<emphasis id="B95BEAB269588F5FFDDEFA63FCC1818B" box="[594,867,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Eucelatoria obrumbrata</emphasis>
(Wulp)
</taxonomicName>
species group (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBE4B5169588F5FFBE4FA63FADF818B" author="Inclan, D. J. &amp; Stireman, J. O. III" box="[1128,1405,1411,1437]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="63 - 97" refId="ref67741" refString="Inclan, D. J. &amp; Stireman, J. O. III (2010) A new species and synonymy of the Neotropical Eucelatoria Townsend and redescription of Myiodoriops Townsend. ZooKeys, 464, 63 - 97. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 464.8155" type="journal article" year="2010">Inclán &amp; Stireman 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
